The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Gopi set to be chief coach

New Delhi: Former All England badminton champion Pullela Gopichand is set to take over as Indias chief badminton coach for a four-year period. 

Gopichand, one of the finest shuttlers the country has produced, will take over the reins from Vimal Kumar, whose three-year tenure ended with the Thomas Cup in Tokyo last month where India reached the quarter finals. (PTI) 




